    "Understanding the Three Numbers in range()To see exactly how it works, we can replace the formula with actual numbers. Since len(sales) is 5, the code translates to range(4, -1, -1).start = 4 (len(sales) - 1)Python lists start counting at 0.For a list of 5 items, the last index is 4. This is where the loop begins.stop = -1The loop stops before it reaches this number.Because it stops just before -1, the final index it processes is 0 (the first item in your list).step = -1This tells Python to subtract 1 on every turn instead of adding. This makes the loop count down backward.\n",
